Sample IBM Pascal Program Notes:
 
1) The Opt-Tech Sort entry point used with IBM 
and Microsoft Pascal is "SORTIBMP".


Linking IBM & MS Pascal Programs with Opt-Tech Sort

An example of linking the IBM Pascal sample program 
with Opt-Tech Sort is shown below.  

A>LINK
Object Module [.OBJ]: XMSPAS [+ SWnnK]                   
Run File [XMSPAS.EXE]:     (press enter)
List File [NUL.MAP]:       (press enter)
Libraries [.LIB]:SORT

A sortwork area (SWnnK) may not be required when 
linking.  Please see 'Linking Opt-Tech Sort' and 
'Memory Considerations' in Chapter Four.
